  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: For send command in 1:1 chat: it's possible to modify recipient, asset and amount if cancel transaction signing on Send transaction screen. The outcomes are different but both are wrong in release build and in PR build:\r\n1. In release build: old amount and asset are shown as sent. E.g. /send ETH 10 was modified to 0 ETH but 1:1 chat shows that 10 ETH was sent\r\n2. in PR #4918 build: no message is shown in 1:1 chat if user taps on Cancel and modifies some or none of the fields. \r\n\r\nNote: we had an issue that it was possible to edit read-only fields before and it was fixed in https://github.com/status-im/status-react/pull/4761\r\n\r\n\r\nExample for release build 10 (amount is shown as 0.09 ETH but 0 ETH was sent)\r\n![screenshot_20180624-140741](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6584810/41818964-e6ed4288-77b8-11e8-8ba4-c3532eacb66a.png)\r\n![screenshot_20180624-140735](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6584810/41818966-eb2191d8-77b8-11e8-8a91-9cb8282432b2.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nContact, amount and asset should be readonly on Send transaction screen if transaction was initiated from 1:1 chat. Even if Cancel sign or type wrong password or do any other actions on this screen, fields should stay readonly.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nContent in readonly fields recipient, asset and amount can be modified if tap on Cancel \r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\nYou need to have someone in Contacts and test ETH and STT.\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Open 1:1 chat\r\n- /send ETH 0.09 and send. As a result, Send transaction screen is shown with prompt to enter password\r\n- tap on Cancel (so no password is entered)\r\n- tap on each of readonly fields Recipient, Asset and Amount to check that you can modify them. Note that currently on Android Amount field can be modified and on iOS you need to try to change Asset first and then Amount field can be modified.\r\n\r\nTF session for release build: https://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803622-status/builds/8504010/sessions/4394703958/?accessToken=Xrj5/RdY970acblxw-dz40ujPe8\r\nTF for build https://github.com/status-im/status-react/pull/4918#issuecomment-399655747 : https://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803622-status/builds/8504437/sessions/4394704219/?accessToken=BeThUmYi3OklH5jSs3f/DlJ9Zts\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: \r\n1. Release build 10 with TF. https://jenkins.status.im/job/status-react/job/public-beta-1-testfairy/10/\r\n2. PR build https://github.com/status-im/status-react/pull/4918#issuecomment-399655747\r\n* Operating System: Android and iOS\r\n\r\n<blockquote><div><strong><a href=\"https://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803622-status/builds/8504010/sessions/4394703958/?accessToken=Xrj5/RdY970acblxw-dz40ujPe8\">TestFairy: Status 0.9.21 (6108) @2018</a></strong></div></blockquote>\r\n<blockquote><img src=\"/static/f03d97b6/favicon.ico\" width=\"48\" align=\"right\"><div><strong><a href=\"https://jenkins.status.im/job/status-react/job/public-beta-1-testfairy/10/\">status-react Â» public-beta-1-testfairy #10 [Jenkins]</a></strong></div></blockquote>",
